a.xlink:title: Calculation of the net asset value for an investment fund/fund class.
Security that is a sub-set of an investment fund, and is governed by the same investment fund policy, for example, a dividend option or valuation currency.
Amount of money due to the government or tax authority, according to various pre-defined parameters such as thresholds or income.
Statistical data related to the price change of a security.
Performance factors of the investment fund / fund class.
Characteristics related to the price of the security.

Consideration, such as amount of money, paid or received in exchange for an asset that has been invested, loaned or borrowed for a certain period. The interest is expressed as a fixed amount or percentage of the amount upon which the interest is applied.
Cash movements from or to a fund as a result of investment funds transactions, for example, subscriptions or redemptions.
